article.headline: Houston 77, Marshall 61
article.story: HUNTINGTON, W.Va. (AP) -- Robert McKiver scored 19 points and all five Houston starters finished in double figures in 77-61 win over Marshall on Saturday night. Oliver Lafayette scored 16 points before fouling out for Houston (9-9, 4-2 Conference USA). Jahmar Thorpe scored 12, Marcus Malone had 11 and Dion Dowell 10. Mark Dorris scored 21 points for Marshall (7-13, 2-4) and Markel Humphrey had 15. With the score tied 7-7, Houston used a full-court press to take over, forcing 13 first-half turnovers and jumping to a 27-12 lead midway through the first half. Lafayette scored 13 first-half points as Houston raced to a 44-26 halftime lead. Marshall trimmed the deficit to 65-56 with 4:38 remaining in the game before Malone hit 3-pointers 1:22 apart to push the lead back to 15. Houston made 18-of-22 free throws and 11 3-pointers. McKiver went 11-of-12 from the line. Marshall shot 33 percent from the floor.
